<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="66" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1500,1767]" pageId="7" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,320,1581,1607]" pageId="7" pageNumber="66">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[326,568,1581,1606]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Heradion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flammeum" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[326,568,1581,1606]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="66">Heradion flammeum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[575,705,1581,1607]" pageId="7" pageNumber="66">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is here considered a member of the 
<taxonomicName box="[1126,1212,1581,1606]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Heradion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="naiadis">
<emphasis box="[1126,1212,1581,1606]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="66">naiadis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
­group by the presence of a small, triangular DTA on the male palpal organ. The species can be easily recognized by: the relatively small, triangular DTA (apparently the smallest comparing to other members of the species­group) (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1601,1625]" captionTargetBox="[177,1421,183,1587]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,178,1592]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 12. Apices of tegulum, showing median apophyses and distal tegular apophyses (5 – 9): Heradion peteri (5); H. naiadis (6); H. intermedium spec. nov. (7); H. flammeum comb. nov. (8); H. paradiseum comb. nov. (9). Retrolateral view of tibiae, showing VTA and RTA: H. paradiseum comb. nov. (10); H. flammeum comb. nov. (11); H. intermedium spec. nov. Abbreviations: DTA: distal tegular apophysis; m, membranous area; MA: median apophysis; RTA: retrolateral tibial apophysis; T, tegulum; VTA, ventrolateral tibial apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175337/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="66">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,167,1701,1727]" pageId="7" pageNumber="66" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
); the sickle­shaped MA with upper braches bending inward (
<figureCitation box="[884,955,1701,1727]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1601,1625]" captionTargetBox="[177,1421,183,1587]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,178,1592]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 12. Apices of tegulum, showing median apophyses and distal tegular apophyses (5 – 9): Heradion peteri (5); H. naiadis (6); H. intermedium spec. nov. (7); H. flammeum comb. nov. (8); H. paradiseum comb. nov. (9). Retrolateral view of tibiae, showing VTA and RTA: H. paradiseum comb. nov. (10); H. flammeum comb. nov. (11); H. intermedium spec. nov. Abbreviations: DTA: distal tegular apophysis; m, membranous area; MA: median apophysis; RTA: retrolateral tibial apophysis; T, tegulum; VTA, ventrolateral tibial apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175337/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="66">
Fig. 
<number box="[939,955,1701,1727]" pageId="7" pageNumber="66" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
); the RTA not fully formed (
<figureCitation box="[1292,1378,1701,1727]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1601,1625]" captionTargetBox="[177,1421,183,1587]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,178,1592]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 12. Apices of tegulum, showing median apophyses and distal tegular apophyses (5 – 9): Heradion peteri (5); H. naiadis (6); H. intermedium spec. nov. (7); H. flammeum comb. nov. (8); H. paradiseum comb. nov. (9). Retrolateral view of tibiae, showing VTA and RTA: H. paradiseum comb. nov. (10); H. flammeum comb. nov. (11); H. intermedium spec. nov. Abbreviations: DTA: distal tegular apophysis; m, membranous area; MA: median apophysis; RTA: retrolateral tibial apophysis; T, tegulum; VTA, ventrolateral tibial apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175337/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="66">
Fig. 
<number box="[1347,1378,1701,1727]" pageId="7" pageNumber="66" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
); the blunt VTA provided with a group of long setae (not shown here).
</paragraph>
